cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DS, cs.SY. 

This paper presents a choreographic approach for programming updatable, distributed applications. The paper focuses on the theoretical model and implementation of the programming framework. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the implementation of the programming framework, which involves the use of a process-level language and a runtime environment. This suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Additionally, the paper discusses the properties of the generated distributed applications, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
